{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 09:47:19.343325", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submission completed.\n\nSummary of submitted solution:\n- is_anomaly: true\n- faulty_devices: server_access_router, dns_server, router_core_1, router_dist_1_1, load_balancer, web_server_0, web_server_1, web_server_2, web_server_3\n- root_cause_name: dns_record_error, ospf_area_misconfiguration, load_balancer_overload, receiver_resource_contention\n\nNotes:\n- The submission maps the direct-access policy violation to DNS/routing configuration issues (dns_record_error and ospf_area_misconfiguration anchored at dns_server and server_access_router).\n- The HTTP latency and host-specific jitter are attributed to possible load balancer/backend processing delays and path device contention (load_balancer_overload, receiver_resource_contention, with router_core_1 and router_dist_1_1 included for the host_1 path jitter).", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 3920, "output_tokens": 185, "total_tokens": 4105, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 3712}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
